# StrictDoc HTML Output Location

## Requirement

Generated HTML files SHALL be stored in a separate `requirements_html/` directory.

The HTML directory structure SHALL mirror the source document structure.

## Directory Structure

HTML output SHALL follow this structure:

```
requirements_html/
├── srs/              # HTML output for System Requirements
│   └── SRS001.html
├── sss/              # HTML output for Software Requirements
│   └── SSS001.html
├── sdd/              # HTML output for Design Documents
│   └── SDD001.html
├── irs/              # HTML output for Interface Requirements
│   └── IRS001.html
├── tp/               # HTML output for Test Plans
│   └── TP001.html
└── td/               # HTML output for Test Descriptions
    └── TD001.html
```

## Source to HTML Mapping

Each `.sdoc` source file SHALL have a corresponding HTML file in the `requirements_html/` directory.

The HTML file SHALL be located in the same subdirectory structure as the source file.

For example:
- `requirements/srs/SRS001.sdoc` → `requirements_html/srs/SRS001.html`
- `requirements/sss/SSS001.sdoc` → `requirements_html/sss/SSS001.html`

## HTML Output Configuration

StrictDoc SHALL be configured to output HTML to the `requirements_html/` directory.

The HTML output directory SHALL be specified in StrictDoc configuration (e.g., `strictdoc.toml` or `strictdoc_config.py`).

## HTML File Maintenance

HTML files SHALL be regenerated whenever source `.sdoc` files are modified.

HTML files SHALL be committed to version control alongside source files.

HTML files SHALL NOT be manually edited; all changes SHALL be made to source `.sdoc` files.
